## Codebase discoveries
- On read-back, persisted `attributes` always include an SDK-injected `weave`
  metadata block (client_version, source=python-sdk, os/sys info); with no user
  attributes it is exactly {"weave": {...}} (get_calls fetches it; column-limited
  queries return {}). Persisted `summary` gains a server-computed `weave` block
  (status/trace_name/latency_ms); the client-side `status_counts` rollup uses
  TraceStatus(str, Enum) keys, so enum keys == their string values.

